         VT would need to be redesigned if it does go to a random spawn. The warder system really screws up any attempts to randomize things.</P><P>If warders spawning/despawning are triggered by their associated named mob being dead, and that spawning is random, that generally means that people won't start the zone until the first blob spawns and they can be assured they won't get hit by a warder pop.</P><P>It will happen though, I think. The big non-US guild on my server recently got themselves enough keys to clear VT, and since then they've gotten every aten spawn. Once enough people start bitching at Verant about it, across enough servers, it will change.</P><P>Would be nice if the game was designed such that time zones didn't matter, but as they say if you put wishes in one hand and shit in the other, the one with shit fills up first.</P><P></P><P><a href="http://tru7h.org/absor/" target="_blank">http://tru7h.org/absor/</a> -  ask absor anything!<BR><a href="http://xzzy.org/ereet/" target="_blank">http://xzzy.org/ereet/</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
